dColor>#92846e</BackgroundColor><VerticalAlign>Middle</VerticalAlign><PaddingLeft>2pt</PaddingLeft><PaddingRight>2pt</PaddingRight><PaddingTop>2pt</PaddingTop><PaddingBottom>2pt</PaddingBottom></Style></Textbox><Textbox Name="Textbox91"><CanGrow>true</CanGrow><KeepTogether>true</KeepTogether><Paragraphs><Paragraph><TextRuns><TextRun><Value>Guaranteed Value (USD)</Value><Style><FontFamily>calibri light</FontFamily><FontSize>8pt</FontSize><FontWeight>Bold</FontWeight></Style></TextRun></TextRuns><Style><TextAlign>Center</TextAlign></Style></Paragraph></Paragraphs><rd:DefaultName>Textbox72</rd:DefaultName><Top>5.27722in</Top><Left>1.87453in</Left><Height>0.25833in</Height><Width>6.16103in</Width><ZIndex>22</ZIndex><Style><Border><Color>White</Color><Style>Solid</Style></Border><TopBorder><Style>Solid</Style><Width>1pt</Width></TopBorder><BottomBorder><Style>Solid</Style><Width>1pt</Width></BottomBorder><LeftBorder><Style>Solid</Style><Width>1pt</Width></LeftBorder><RightBorder><Style>Solid</Style><Width>1pt</Width></RightBorder><BackgroundColor>#92846e</BackgroundColor><VerticalAlign>Middle</VerticalAlign><PaddingLeft>2pt</PaddingLeft><PaddingRight>2pt</PaddingRight><PaddingTop>2pt</PaddingTop><PaddingBottom>2pt</PaddingBottom></Style></Textbox><Textbox Name="Textbox93"><CanGrow>true</CanGrow><KeepTogether>true</KeepTogether><Paragraphs><Paragraph><TextRuns><TextRun><Value>* Premium illustrated in the above table includes both Basic benefit, WoP benefit and All Rider Benefits</Value><Style><FontFamily>Calibri Light</FontFamily><FontSize>8pt</FontSize></Style></TextRun></TextRuns><Style /></Paragraph></Paragraphs><rd:DefaultName>Textbox93</rd:DefaultName><Top>7.47999in</Top><Left>0.20777in</Left><Height>0.25in</Height><Width>5.38331in</Width><ZIndex>23</ZIndex><Style><Border><Style>None</Style></Border><PaddingLeft>2pt</PaddingLeft><PaddingRight>2pt</PaddingRight><PaddingTop>2pt</PaddingTop><PaddingBottom>2pt</PaddingBottom></Style></Textbox><Textbox Name="Textbox95"><CanGrow>true</CanGrow><KeepTogether>true</KeepTogether><Paragraphs><Paragraph><TextRuns><TextRun><Value>IMPORTANT NOTES:</Value><Style><FontFamily>Calibri Light</FontFamily><FontSize>8pt</FontSize><FontWeight>Bold</FontWeight></Style></TextRun></TextRuns><Style /></Paragraph><Paragraph><TextRuns><TextRun><Value /><Style><FontFamily>Calibri Light</FontFamily><FontSize>8pt</FontSize></Style></TextRun></TextRuns><Style /></Paragraph><Paragraph><TextRuns><TextRun><Value>The premiums as mentioned above are for standard health as per the Company's guidelines.  You may have to pay additional/ extra premiums after the underwriting assessment of your policy.						
The above benefits are illustrated with the assumption that all the premiums are timely and adequately paid.						
The above Surrender Value is illustrated at the end of each respective policy year. It is the amount of money that the Policy Owner receives if he/she surrrenders his/her Insurance Policy while the Policy is still inforce. Once the surrender benefit is paid, the policy is terminated, and all benefits of this policy cease to exist.												
Should you decide not to continue with this Policy, you could cancel it within 30 days from the Issuance Date of the Life Insurance Certificate. This period is known as the Free-Look Period. In case the Policy is cancelled within the Free-Look Period, we shall refund to the Policy Owner : i) all premium received by the Company without any interest; minus ii) related health-check and examination expenses, if any.												
Buying a life insurance policy is a long-term financial commitment. An early surrender of the Policy usually involves high costs and the Surrender Value payable may be less than the total premiums paid.												
Once the Total and Permanent Disability (TPD) benefit of the Basic Plan or Rider is paid, the Death benefit of the Basic Plan or Rider ceases to exist.												
Advanced Cash Back is the periodic cash payments that are payable to the Policy Owner at the end of every three policy years (except at maturity date) while the Policy is still inforce.  												
Should you surrender during the policy year where Advanced Cash Back is payable, no Advanced Cash Back is payable after surrender.												
In case the Waiver of Premium (WoP) benefit is provided, all the remaining future premiums due of the whole policy will be waived after the Policy Owner's death or Total and Permanent Disability.												
In case the Family Protection Rider is attached to the Basic Plan, in the event of death or TPD of this Rider’s Life Insured not caused by an accident, 100% of this Rider’s Sum Insured is payable. In case of death or TPD of this Rider’s Life Insured due to an accident, 200% of the Sum Insured is payable. No maturity benefit is payable for this Rider.					In case the Family Income Rider is attached to the Basic Plan, in the event of death or TPD of this Rider’s Life Insured, the company will pay a yearly amount of money equals to this rider’s Sum Insured starting from the next anniversary date after the death/TPD of this Rider's Life Insured until maturity date. No maturity benefit is payable for this Rider.																								
The exclusions for Death, Accidental Death, and Total and Permanent Disability (TPD) benefits are detailed in the Policy Terms and Conditions of the Basic Plan and/or attached Rider(s).												
In case the Family Care Rider is attached to the Basic Plan, in the event Rider’s Life Insured suffers from Early Stage Critical Illness (CI) condition, 50% of this Rider’s Sum Insured is payable. In the event of Late Stage CI condition of the Rider’s Life Insured, 150% of this Rider’s Sum Insured is payable (less the amount payable for Early CI).</Value><Style><FontFamily>Calibri Light</FontFamily><FontSize>8pt</FontSize></Style></TextRun></TextRuns><Style /></Paragraph><Paragraph><TextRuns><TextRun><Value>In case the Hospital Care Rider is attached to the Basic Plan, in the event the Rider’s Life Insured is being hospitalized due to accidental or CI reasons, 100% of this Rider’s Sum Insured is payable for each day of admission or 200% of this Rider’s Sum Insured is payable for each admission day of being in Intensive Care Unit (ICU). In the event the Rider’s Life Insured undergoes surgery during admission due to CI or accidental reasons, 300% of this Rider’s Sum Insured is payable one time in an admission. In case this Rider’s Life Insured having selected for outpatient treatment, 100% of Sum Insured is payable per day of outpatient.												
This illustration will form part of the policy contract and must be read in conjunction with the Policy Terms and Conditions of the Basic Plan and/or attached Rider(s).												
